race.comment: CASH (6) returns gelded for the Hickmott camp and looks highly promising. Blitzed his rivals in his Balaklava trial, which was the quickest of the day, and Pannell reunites. Sure to be prominent and very hard to beat. THUNDER SHOC (10) wasn't given much hope last start when drifting back to last but did make strong late inroads. If able to settle closer this time, his turn of foot makes him a genuine threat. GINGER SINNER (3) is in terrific form chasing a hat-trick. Rock-hard fit and a distance specialist, he'll put his best foot forward again. DANCING STORM (2) is another chasing three straight. Needs a smart steer from Toeroek but deserves respect. THE STALKER (9) has been solid in two runs back and should give backers another sight.
